ENTRY            12986   20260122   20260316   20260316       1526
SUBENT        12986001   20260122   20260316   20260316       1526
BIB                 13         20
TITLE      Cross Sections For Neutron Producing Reactions
           Induced by 6- And 10-MeV Neutrons Incident on 10B and
           11B
AUTHOR     (M.Drosg,P.W.Lisowski,D.M.Drake,R.A.Hardekopf,
           S.M.Muellner)
REFERENCE  (R,LA-10665-MS,1986)
REL-REF    (O,14719001,P.W.Lisowski+,J,NSE,195,1131,2021) More
           comprehensive analysis.
INSTITUTE  (1USALAS,2AUSIRK)
FACILITY   (VDGT,1USALAS) Tandem Van-de-Graaff
INC-SOURCE (P-T)
DETECTOR   (SCIN) The NE213 neutron detector.
METHOD     (TOF) 2.5-m flight path.
MONITOR    (1-H-1(N,EL)1-H-1,,SIG) at 35 degr.
CORRECTION Corrected for multiple scattering.
STATUS     (APRVD) Approved by P.W.Lisowski on January 23, 2026.
HISTORY    (19860908C)
           (20260122A) BP: Updated entry to the current EXFOR
           format, added subentries 8-13, corrected INSITUTE:
           2AUSPVI -> 2AUSIRK and contacted author.
ENDBIB              20
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           23
SUBENT        12986002   20260122   20260316   20260316       1526
BIB                  4         11
REACTION   (5-B-10(N,X)0-NN-1,,SIG)
ANALYSIS   (INTAD) The integrations over the solid angle were
           done by fitting the angular distributions by means of
           Legendre polynomials Pi so that the integrated cross
           section was obtained from the first coefficient A0
           after multiplying by 4pi.
